---
import DocsNav from "../../components/DocsNav.astro";
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import { repositoryUrl } from "../../data/site";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Getting started — Loom Kernels"
  description="Build, validate, and embed Loom Kernels from Rust, CUDA, or PyTorch."
>
  <header class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Documentation / Start</p>
    <h1>From contract to CUDA launch.</h1>
    <p>
      Loom Kernels is an inference operator backend, not an inference engine or
      tensor framework. Start with the dependency-light Rust core; enable CUDA
      only on a qualified accelerator host.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="docs-layout">
    <DocsNav active="Start" />
    <article class="prose">
      <h2>Workspace layers</h2>
      <div class="doc-grid">
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h3>loom-kernels</h3>
          <p>Public contracts, capability queries, and deterministic CPU references.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h3>loom-cuda</h3>
          <p>Safe stream and buffer ownership, checked dispatch, and benchmarks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h3>loom-cuda-sys</h3>
          <p>Raw CUDA ABI and compilation plumbing with minimal dependencies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h3>python</h3>
          <p>Current-stream PyTorch operators and narrow vLLM integration points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>CPU contract gates</h2>
      <p>
        The default workspace does not require a CUDA toolkit. It validates
        shape, dtype, buffer, and numerical reference behavior first.
      </p>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/feichai0017/loom-kernels.git
cd loom-kernels

cargo fmt --all -- --check
cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings
cargo test --workspace --all-targets
cargo check --workspace --release</code></pre>

      <h2>CUDA qualification</h2>
      <p>
        Set the toolkit and architecture explicitly. The example below targets
        Hopper compute capability 9.0 and runs correctness before CUDA-event timing.
      </p>
      <pre><code>CUDA_HOME=/usr/local/cuda-13.1 \
LOOM_CUDA_ARCHS=90 \
cargo bench -p loom-cuda --features cuda \
  --bench silu_and_mul_dynamic_fp8 -- \
  --dtype bf16 --rows 8 --width 11008 --group-size 128 \
  --warmup 100 --iterations 1000 --samples 9</code></pre>

      <h2>Read the contracts</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href={`${repositoryUrl}/blob/main/docs/design/operator-library.md`}>architecture document</a>
        {" "}defines public admission gates. The{" "}
        <a href={`${repositoryUrl}/blob/main/docs/operator-catalog.md`}>operator catalog</a>
        {" "}separates supported, next, planned, profile-gated, and vendor-backed work.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
